WEBVTT

00:09.460 --> 00:13.260
Hi there! Welcome to
this video. Today we

00:13.260 --> 00:14.720
will learn about
different types of

00:14.720 --> 00:17.320
social engineering.
Knowing the types

00:17.320 --> 00:20.040
helps you recognize
attacks more easily.

00:20.420 --> 00:22.840
The goal of this
video is to show

00:22.840 --> 00:25.280
common types of
social engineering.

00:25.400 --> 00:27.800
We will look at how
they work and what

00:27.800 --> 00:30.520
warning signs to
watch for. This will

00:30.520 --> 00:32.700
help you make safer
choices.

00:37.900 --> 00:39.880
Social engineering
does not look the

00:39.880 --> 00:42.040
same every time.
Attackers change

00:42.040 --> 00:43.400
their tricks
depending on the

00:43.400 --> 00:46.740
situation. But the
goal is always to

00:46.740 --> 00:50.380
influence people.
Urgency attacks try

00:50.380 --> 00:52.660
to make people act
quickly. They say

00:52.660 --> 00:55.860
things like, act now,
or your account will

00:55.860 --> 00:59.060
be closed. Urgency
stops people from

00:59.060 --> 01:02.700
thinking carefully.
Impersonation is when

01:02.700 --> 01:05.280
attackers pretend to
be someone else. They

01:05.280 --> 01:07.660
might pretend to be a
teacher, a company,

01:07.660 --> 01:09.980
or a friend. This
makes people trust

01:09.980 --> 01:13.080
them more easily.
Some attacks promise

01:13.080 --> 01:15.880
prizes or rewards.
They may say you won

01:15.880 --> 01:19.100
something or earned a
bonus. The goal is to

01:19.100 --> 01:21.120
make you share
information or click

01:21.120 --> 01:24.500
a link. Fear-based
messages try to scare

01:24.500 --> 01:26.940
people. They warn
about problems,

01:26.940 --> 01:29.640
trouble, or loss.
Fear can make people

01:29.640 --> 01:33.140
react without
checking. Curiosity

01:33.140 --> 01:34.740
tricks make people
wonder what will

01:34.740 --> 01:38.000
happen next. Messages
like, look at this,

01:38.000 --> 01:40.720
or see what you
missed, are examples.

01:40.720 --> 01:43.900
Curiosity can lead to
risky clicks.

01:44.280 --> 01:46.200
Different attacks
look different

01:46.200 --> 01:48.660
because people are
different. Attackers

01:48.660 --> 01:50.940
choose tricks that
match the situation.

01:50.940 --> 01:53.600
But the warning signs
are often similar.

01:57.660 --> 02:00.860
Warning signs include
urgency, pressure,

02:00.860 --> 02:03.480
requests for personal
information, messages

02:03.480 --> 02:06.160
from unknown senders,
or offers that seem

02:06.160 --> 02:09.640
too good to be true.
Noticing these signs

02:09.640 --> 02:14.080
is an important skill
. These attacks can

02:14.080 --> 02:16.280
appear in emails,
messages, games, and

02:16.280 --> 02:18.540
social media. They
can also happen on

02:18.540 --> 02:21.540
school platforms or
phone calls. No place

02:21.540 --> 02:23.180
is completely risk
-free.

02:28.860 --> 02:31.380
When you notice
warning signs, slow

02:31.380 --> 02:34.360
down. Do not reply,
click, or share

02:34.360 --> 02:37.640
information right
away. Checking first

02:37.640 --> 02:41.500
can prevent problems.
If you are unsure,

02:41.500 --> 02:44.680
ask a trusted adult
for help. Trusted

02:44.680 --> 02:46.540
adults can help you
decide what to do

02:46.540 --> 02:49.460
next. Asking for help
is a smart safety

02:49.460 --> 02:54.300
choice. Let's recap.
Social engineering

02:54.300 --> 02:57.580
has many types. They
often use urgency,

02:57.580 --> 03:00.020
fear, trust, or
curiosity.

03:00.700 --> 03:03.020
Recognizing warning
signs helps you stay

03:03.020 --> 03:06.600
safe. Great work! In
this video, you

03:06.600 --> 03:08.480
learned about types
of social engineering.

03:08.480 --> 03:11.260
Next, you will
practice recognizing

03:11.260 --> 03:13.320
these attacks and
learning how to

03:13.320 --> 03:15.920
respond safely. Thank
you for watching.
